ement occurred within 48 hours, critically obviating the need for surgery. The patient was discharged with proptosis resolved, continuing oral Linezolid and Cefuroxime. This case confirms that prompt, aggressive IV antibiotics are paramount in managing stage 1 and 2 orbital cellulitis and can prevent unnecessary invasive procedures.', '', 'ACUTE BACTERIAL RHINOSINUSITIS MASQUERADING AS ANGIOFIBROMA :  A CASE REPORT', 2, 1, '2025-09-27 11:44:54', '2025-09-27 11:44:57'),
